title: China is close to peak emissions, but it doesn’t want to talk about it
description: A slowing economy and a surge of renewable energy are shrinking China’s carbon footprint. Beijing isn’t bragging, though.

title: Zelensky arrives in Washington as Ukraine aid stalls in Congress
description: Volodymyr Zelensky warned against what he called a potential political betrayal of Ukraine’s military, saying Russia is benefitting from Congress’ inaction.

title: Jailed Russian opposition figure Alexei Navalny is missing, supporters say
description: Supporters say Navalny was in ill health shortly before being removed from the roster of the prison colony where he had been held east of Moscow, and that his lawyers cannot find him.

title: Jubilation and high expectations as Poland marks end of right-wing rule
description: Donald Tusk as prime minister will face challenges fixing relations with the E.U., restoring independence to courts and media, and loosening abortion restrictions.

title: Who is Hamas leader Yehiya Sinwar: From enforcer to Oct. 7 mastermind
description: Interrogation transcripts and accounts from Israeli security officials and fellow prisoners point to an uncompromising strategist with a penchant for killing.

title: Rising Philippine-China tensions in South China Sea: 5 moments from 2023
description: After a collision this weekend between Chinese and Philippine vessels, and the use of water cannons a dozen times, the Philippines condemned the “serious escalation” of Chinese aggression.

title: Israel claims progress against Hamas as humanitarian crisis worsens
description: Israeli forces are signaling optimism in their battle against Hamas in the Gaza Strip, but the humanitarian toll has been steadily rising.

title: China’s cyber army is invading critical U.S. services
description: The intrusions are part of a broader effort to develop ways to sow chaos or snarl logistics in the event of a U.S.-China conflict in the Pacific, officials say.

title: Israel used U.S.-supplied white phosphorus in Lebanon attack
description: An analysis of shell fragments shows Israel used U.S.-made white phosphorus munitions in an attack that a rights group says should be investigated as a war crime.

title: Whistleblowing doctor who revealed China’s AIDS epidemic dies at 95
description: Gao Yaojie was exiled from China after she exposed an AIDS epidemic in the 1990s linked to a poorly managed blood transfusion program.

title: Israel-Gaza war live updates: State of Gaza’s health system prompts dire warnings as fierce fighting rages
description: Israel’s military claims to have hit 250 targets in the past day, including in southern Gaza. The WHO warned that the enclave’s health-care system is near collapse.

title: How the Venezuela-Guyana border almost started a U.S.-British war
description: Last week, Venezuelan President Nicolás Maduro threatened to annex nearly three-quarters of neighboring Guyana. One origin of the longstanding border dispute stems from a U.S. intervention more than a century ago, during which Washington was on the side of Venezuela — not Guyana.
